Package com.cubeia.firebase.api.util

Interface Summary
ConfigSource A configuration source represents a single source of configuration for an artifact.
ConfigSourceListener A listener for configuration sources.
MapActor<E>  
ResourceLocator This interface is used by games or services to locate resources within their GAR/SAR archives.
StringList The string list is a simple typed unmodifiable list, used by the configuration system to provide a comma-separated list of string values.
UnmodifiableList<T> A simple iterable interface for unmodifiable lists.
UnmodifiableSet<T> A simple iterable interface for unmodifiable sets.
 

Class Summary
ActorMap<E>  
Arguments Simple utility class for argument bounds checking.
ClassPathConfig A very simple config source that takes a string argument and attempt to load the source from the class path.
ConcurrentHashSet<E> A simple Set implementation backed by a ConcurrentHashMap to deal with the fact that the JDK does not have a proper concurrent Set implementation that uses efficient lock striping.
ConfigSourceAdapter NB: This class is within the public API because of build reasons, it should only be used for testing! It will be moved shortly.
FileConfigSource A simple configuration source based on a file.
HitCounter This class is used for counting hits of different events and printing the statistics.
ParameterUtil A small utility class for handling parameters and their IO representation.
Range<T> A very simple range class.
ScheduledAction<T extends Action> A simple "struct" like bean for pairing a scheduled action with the initial delay it was scheduled for.
SecondCounter  
SocketAddress A simple utility class representing an socket and an address.
TableInterceptorAdapter This is an adapter class for a table interceptor.
TableListenerAdapter This is an adapter class for a table listener.
TaskRepeater This simple utility executes a task one or more times.
TimeCounter  
TimeWindowCounter  
TournamentTableListenerAdapter This is an adapter class for a tournament table listener.
